{"id":568884789,"lang":"java","time":"2 months, 1 week","timestamp":1633877619,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/568884789/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"39.8 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode resultNode = new ListNode(0);\n        ListNode l3 = resultNode;\n\n        int carry = 0;\n\n        while (l1 != null || l2 != null) {\n            int l1_val = l1 != null ? l1.val : 0;\n            int l2_val = l2 != null ? l2.val : 0;\n\n            int sum = l1_val + l2_val + carry;\n\n            int value = sum % 10;\n\n            l3.next = new ListNode(value);\n            carry = sum / 10;\n\n            if (l1 != null) l1 = l1.next;\n            if (l2 != null) l2 = l2.next;\n\n            l3 = l3.next;\n\n        }\n\n        if (carry != 0) {\n            l3.next = new ListNode(carry);\n        }\n        return resultNode.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
